<br>
<br>
First off, IP is getting really TIGHT for me.  I am almost living above my means.  I have been maxing: everything in basic ( plan to cut int and psy and possibly sense out soon, and nano pool ), MA, Brawl, Dimache, phys init, all evades, runspeed, first aid, treatment.  I raise nano skills whenever I can use a new nano.  I also raised vehicle air to 59 and got some air implants ( im sorry for being a twink :&lt;, yalms are a must have heh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  I think im gonna have to cut something once I get higher, so that Ill have enough IPs to go around. I havent touched nano init yet, im scared of the amount of IP it will take <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , yet I know it will be a neccessary evil later on.  Is IP always this tight? Is there anything im maxing that I shouldnt be?<br>
<br>
Second, I have heard stories about lots of MA's who raise shotgun and keep a self-equippable ithica or vektor in inventory for when they get rooted in pvp.  I am currently not planning on becoming a full shotgun MA, but as I plan to spend most of my time pvping, will it be a good idea when I have some extra IP?  I don't want to resort to using incompetence to break root, and I dont think bow's are very good. If shotgun is a good idea, what level would be a good time to dump IP into it?  Right now im guessing whenever I am able to cast SG ( Subconcious Guidance ).<br>
<br>
Third, Right now im wearing full omni-med suit.  No ac, but it has 78 treatment and first aid.  I am getting hit for alot harder, but I can heal myself to max with a first aid or treatment kit.  What level will ac be &gt; higher first aid?<br>
<br>
Fourth ( *pant pant* ), rings. I know that MA gets buffs that make their fists do different type of damage.  Does this mean that I should go for a ring of the elements over a ring of melee?<br>
<br>
