<br>
I'm an old, crusty MA, and haven't played much in the last couple months, but I'll answer what questions I can for you. Actually, the answer to most of them is that it's all up to you - whether/when to use a shotgun, for example, is a difficult choice to make, but personally I wouldn't consider it until after level 130 or so. Until then I don't think we really have enough spare IPs to make the gun worthwhile. At the very least, play your MA for a while longer, get a lot of PvP in, and discover the vast ownage potential of a good old-fashioned lowbie Martial Arts MA.<br>
<br>
As to IPs being tight...That's the way it's going to be for a long, long time if you want to make the most effective MA possible. That said, there are times when IPs will be more scarce, always right before your skills max for your title. At 12 your skills should start maxing out, so you'll have some IPs to spare pretty soon, but keep in mind that your next title is at 50 and don't waste them. Basically there is a point in every title where IPs are in short supply.<br>
<br>
I can't help you too much with the Omni-Med suit thing; when I was a lowbie I never played with one on all the time. My guess is that the point beyond which armor will be more helpful is fast approaching; I would say by 20 or so you'll want to take off the med gear.<br>
<br>
As to the rings, that might be a question for a more up-to-date MA :P It also might require some real testing to find out which is more effective. Personally, I've used defense rings for a good long time, and I'm not about to do any experimentation at this point.<br>
